  "title": "Power of a Test",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which statement about the power of a significance test is true?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i5",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A test performed at a significance level of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"alpha equals 0.01\"><math alttext=\"alpha equals 0.01\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0.01</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> has a higher power than the same test performed at a significance level of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"alpha equals 0.05\"><math alttext=\"alpha equals 0.05\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0.05</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">If the probability of Type <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>I</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> error is decreased, the power of the test is increased.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The power of a test is equal to the probability of making a Type <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>II</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> error.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The power of a test is independent of the sample size.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The power of a test at a particular parameter value increases as the distance from the hypothesized value to the parameter value increases.</p>",
        "value": "i5"
      }
    ]
